The President signed three bills into law on March 18, 2022. The first is H.R. 189, the "John Lewis NIMHD Research Endowment Revitalization Act of 2021," which allows former centers of excellence to be eligible for minority health research endowment. The second is H.R. 1667, the "Dr. Lorna Breen Health Care Provider Protection Act," which authorizes programs to improve mental and behavioral health among health care providers. The third is H.R. 2497, the "Amache National Historic Site Act," which establishes the Amache National Historic Site in Colorado to preserve and interpret the incarceration of civilians of Japanese ancestry during World War II. The President expressed gratitude to the Representatives and Senators who showed leadership in these efforts.